    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-09-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-09-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="604"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.232/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-09-17T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1927—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Embassy’s telegram number 42 of September 12.<note n="11" xml:id="d604fn11"
                        >Not printed.</note> Received note from Foreign Office today which states
                    that the Government of Peru is willing to negotiate treaty as soon as possible.
                    The note adds that Peru desires that in the proposed treaty we grant to Peruvian
                    sugar the same treatment which is now conceded to Cuban sugar. Will the
                    Department please telegraph me its views for my confidential information and
                    guidance before negotiations start? Texts of notes exchanged will go forward in
                    next pouch.<note n="11" xml:id="d604fn12">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
